            <div class="Facts">
                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                Pempek Palembang is a celebrated dish originating from the city of Palembang in South Sumatra, 
                Indonesia, renowned for its delightful fusion of flavors and textures. Crafted from a harmonious blend 
                of ground fish, typically mackerel or tenggiri, combined with tapioca flour, eggs, and a medley of aromatic 
                spices like garlic and ground pepper, pempek embodies culinary craftsmanship at its finest. What distinguishes
                 Pempek Palembang is its diverse array of shapes and sizes, each bearing its own name and unique characteristics. 
                 From the iconic Pempek Kapal to the sumptuous Pempek Lenjer, every variant promises a sensorial journey that 
                 tantalizes the taste buds and captures the essence of Palembang's rich culinary heritage.
                </p>
